{
  "stem": "20021.3",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You heard of cases like this all the time, somebody being shot here, somebody being shot there.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They would arrive in a car, round up whoever they saw, kill, kill, kill, and all that.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So that was mostly to spread fear, you know, and maybe their savage pleasure.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But all of this until the-- the official resettlement and Holocaust started in Auschwitz and amounted maybe, a town like Tarnow, I would guess at the most over the three years that there were 1,000 people, more like 500, something like that.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I got on the train.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, there was one incident, though, which prompted me mostly to do that.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "About, oh, a month or three weeks before I left, this German who owned my father's factory had with him two girls who were his concubines or lovers or whatever-- not officially married to them, but they both lived with him.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And one day, one of those walks in into-- I worked in a place which was foundry and a repair shop together, you know.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And in other words, they had horses there-- my father had a lot of horses and carts also.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So this place repaired the carts and provided, you know, for horses for what do you call it-- Horseshoes.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Horseshoes, horseshoes for the horse.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I worked in that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And also, every once in a while I would be called upon to fit a key for somebody.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This woman, his secretary, walks in one day, gives me a key, and tells me to fit a key for her.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Now, this was done by hand, unlike here that you do it with a machine, you copy off a machine.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You had to take the two keys and with a file work very closely and do it by hand.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
